\section2 shadow

These properties describe an element's shadow.

\b box-shadow (none | (<length> <length> <length> <length> <color>))

A shorthand to set the shadow of an element to a box-shaped shadow. If set to none,
the shadow will explicitly be disabled. Otherwise, the parameters are X offset, Y offset,
size, blur and finally color.


\section2 shadow-offset

The offset of the shadow from its element. Setting this will move the entire shadow,
as if the light were cast from a different angle.


\section3 shadow-offset-horizontal (<length>)

The horizontal offset of the shadow.

\section3 shadow-offset-vertical (<length>)

The vertical offset of the shadow.


\section3 shadow-color (<color>)

The color of the shadow.

\section3 shadow-size (<length>)

The size of the shadow. This expands the area used for the shadow compared to the element.

\section3 shadow-blur (<length>)

The amount of blur to use for the shadow. Increasing this will increase how smooth the shadow
goes from fully transparent to the full shadow color.





